headline: GE Aerospace and United ink big engine order
summary: Feb. 18—GE Aerospace, a big Southwestern Ohio employer, has inked a deal with one of the nation's biggest airlines. GE said United Airlines has selected 300 GEnx engines to power United's new Boeing 787 Dreamliners.
